15/12/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The European Commission (EC) said on Wednesday (14 December) that it has endorsed the first projects in Croatia financed with funds from the Pre-Accession Instrument for Structural Policies. 
According to the announcement, the EC approved two financial memoranda, under which Croatia would obtain a 51m-euro grant for projects in the environment and transport sectors.
In other news, Croatian Foreign and EU Integration Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic is visiting Sofia, where she met on Wednesday with Bulgarian counterpart Ivaylo Kalfin and Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev. 
Both offered to assist Zagreb in its EU accession efforts. 
(Novi list - 15/12/05; Bulgarian Government Web site, EU Web site, BNR - 14/12/05)
